106.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: From 1905 to 1908 in the Drôme, acts of banditry followed by assassinations by Urbain Liottard, Octave David and Louis Berruyer.
On 31 January 1907 in Paris, eleven-year-old Marthe Erbelding was murdered after being raped and stabbed.
Albert Soleilland was sentenced to death on 23 July 1907. He was pardoned and died in prison in 1920 after 13 years of detention.
On 22 October 1909 in Le Vésinet, the Belgian tenor Jules Godart [fr] was poisoned by Marie Bourette
Marie Bourette was sentenced on 13 July 1910 to forced labor for life by the Seine-et-Oise Assize Court.
On 8 January 1910 in Paris, a police officer was murdered by anarchist Jean-Jacques Liabeuf.
Jean-Jacques Liabeuf was sentenced to death on 4 May 1910 by the Assizes of the Seine. Executed by beheading on 1 July 1910 in Paris.
On 8 September 1910 in Le Havre, Louis Dongé was killed during a fight during a strike.

114.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: On 21 October 1981 in Marseille, investigating judge Pierre Michel was assassinated by an armed commando.
A series of robberies involving hostage-taking by disguised gangsters from 6 October 1981 to 14 January 1986.
Disappearance of three young women, between 1981 and 1986, in the town of Pontcharra in Isère.
Series of rapes and seven murders of young women by Guy Georges.
He has already been the target of two assassination attempts (in Corsica in 1958 and nine years later at his home west of Paris).
Rape and murder of Christelle Bancourt, aged twelve, in June 1982 in Marseille by Christian Marletta.
Sentenced in March 1985 to life imprisonment [fr]. Released in 2006 .
Jean-Pierre Maïone-Libaude, a former member of the Organisation armée secrète (OAS), was assassinated on 13 June 1982 in Argent-sur-Sauldre.
Anti-Semitic attack targeting a Jewish restaurant on Rue des Rosiers in the 4th arrondissement of Paris on 9 August 1982.
The Gang de la Brise de Mer
Sexual abuse of minors in an educational "living space".
Assassination of Bernard Nut, head of the DGSE, shot dead on 15 February 1983 in car in Rigaud.
Abduction of Ludovic Janvier, 6 years old, on 17 March 1983 in Saint-Martin-d'Hères.
One of the Disparus de l'Isère
Guy Orsoni, 24 years old, nationalist activist of the FLNC was tortured then executed.
His assassins were themselves murdered in the Ajaccio remand center [fr].
Disappearance of Grégory Dubrulle on 9 July 1983, at Rue Adrien Ricard in Grenoble.
He regained consciousness the next day, with serious head injuries, in a landfill in Pommiers-la-Placette.
Bomb attack in the south terminal hall of Orly Airport by a Syrian branch of ASALA, causing 8 deaths and more than 56 injuries.
Assassination of the Secrétaire général de préfecture [fr] of Haute-Corse, Pierre-Jean Massimi on 13 September 1983.
Series of rapes in 1983–1984, then a series of rapes and murders in 1995–1999 by Louis Poirson.
Disappearance of Teddy Vrignault, 55 years old, comedian and actor, on 1 November 1984.
Heinous murders of two men on the 7 and 17 December 1984, by two young people, using a young girl, Valérie Subra, serving as their "bait".
The case inspired a book, The Bait, from which The Bait (film, 1995) was taken.
A series of murders of around 21 old ladies from 1984 to 1987 in the Paris region by Thierry Paulin and Jean-Thierry Mathurin.
Paulin, who had AIDS, died before he could be tried. The case inspired I Can't Sleep, released in 1994.
Meurthe-et-Moselle, Moselle, Ardennes, Var, Finistère, Marne, Pas-de-Calais
Series of at least nine murders by Francis Heaulme
Murder of Bernard Hettier by his former mistress in June 1985.
Kidnapping of 5-year-old Anissa Ouadi in Grenoble on 25 June 1985.
Isère missing persons case. She was found drowned on 9 July 1985 in Isère, at the Beauvoir dam.
Kidnapping, sequestration and rape of seven young women, two of whom were murdered, between December 1985 and February 1986.
Georges Courtois [fr] a repeat robber, held around fifteen hostages at the Nantes courthouse with his accomplices, Khalki and Thiolet.
Marie-Élisabeth Cons-Boutboul is sentenced, the 24 March 1994, to 15 years in prison for "complicity in murder".
Kidnapping and rape of two boys and four girls, murder of three girls by Denis Waxin in Lille and its surrounding suburbs.
Serial killer Francis Heaulme was sentenced to life imprisonment on 17 May 2017 for the murder of the two children.
Rapes, murders, assaults and attempted rapes by "the Pockmarked man". notably the murder of Cécile Bloch
On 26 March 2018, Ransom was sentenced to life imprisonment, with a 22-year safety period [fr] after several convictions.
On 5 May 1987 in Neuilly-sur-Marne, Virginie Delmas, 10 years old, was kidnapped. Her body was found naked 5 months later in an orchard.
Investigation ongoing; crime unsolved as of 2025.
Kidnapping of 10-year-old Hemma Davy-Greedharry, 10 years old, in Malakoff on 30 May 1987.
Her burned body was in Châtillon the same day. Case not solved as of 2025.
Abduction of 7-year-old Perrine Vigneron, in Bouleurs, on 3 June 1987.
His body was found in a rapeseed field in Chelles on 27 June 1987. Case not solved as of 2025.
Joël Hipeau was murdered in a staged car accident on 6 June 1987 by Yves Dandonneau to receive his own life insurance.
Abduction of 9-year-old Sabine Dumont in Bièvres on 27 June 1987.
She was found dead, naked, raped in Vauhallan on 28 June 1987. Case not solved as of 2025.

115.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: On 21 March 1991, 8-year-old Charles-Édouard Turquin disappeared in Nice; his body was never found.
Georges Pouille was sentenced on 11 March 2016 to 30 years of criminal imprisonment by the Isère Assize Court.
On 29 May 1991, Abdelali Gasmi, a 26-year-old heroin dealer, had his throat slit in a bar in Marseille.
On 24 June 1991, Ghislaine Marchal, a financially well-off widow, was found dead in the cellar of her villa in Mougins.
Between 6 August 1991 to 25 February 1992, Vincenzo Aiutino murdered three young women in Longwy.
On 25 October 1991, Marie-Claire Bégo, 37, disappeared after getting off her bus in Béard (58160) where she had left her car.
Christiane Séguin was sentenced on 27 May 1998 to 16 years of criminal imprisonment by the Puy-de-Dôme Assize Court.
On 5 April 1992 in Anneville-Ambourville, 40-year-old Sylviane Kaas, was killed at home while her children and husband were at the cinema.
From 30 November 1992 to 13 September 2002 in Beauvais and Saint-Étienne, murder of three men.
The perpetrator, Albert Foulcher, committed suicide on 17 January 2001.
On 21 April 1993, Denise Descaves a college principal was murdered by deputy principal Pierre Dubois in Troyes.
Patrick Trémeau committed the rape and assault of thirteen women in underground car parks in Paris between April 1993 and 29 March 1995.
On 13 May 1993, a hostage-taking in a nursery school by a man identifying himself as "Human Bomb" in Neuilly-sur-Seine.
Erick Schmitt, the perpetrator, was killed by law enforcement on 15 May 1993.
On 8 June 1993, the assassination of the former Vichy police chief René Bousquet in Paris.
Claude Lastennet was sentenced on 22 October 1997 to life imprisonment with a security period of 18 years by the Val-de-Marne Assize Court.
On 25 February 1994, Yann Piat, a former UDF Member of Parliament Yann Piat was assassinated by a mafia commando in Hyères.
In June 1994, 88-year-old Gaston Moysset was murdered at his home in Bezons.
On 5 September 1994, Christian Leprince, his wife Brigitte and two of their daughters, aged ten and six, were murdered in Thorigné.
On 22 September 1994, in Penmarch, Marie-Michèle Calvez's car was found burnt out with the woman's body tied up in the trunk.
The family offered a reward to anyone who can provide any information that can help solve the crime. Crime unsolved as of 2025.
On 26 December 1994, in Marignane, members of the GIA hijacked a plane, followed by a hostage-taking in which three passengers were killed.
The perpetrators, Abdul Yahia, Mustafa Chekienne, Makhlouf Benguetaff and Salim Layadi, were killed by the security forces.
From 1994 to 2006 in Alsace, Yvan Keller killed at least forty elderly women, suffocating them to make them look like natural deaths.
Yvan Keller committed suicide before his trial on 22 September 2006.
On 26 February 1995, Alexi Polevoi murdered six members of his family in Louveciennes.
On 16 May 1995, 37-year-old pregnant woman Carole Prin was murdered in Strasbourg by her companion, Roland Moog.
On 30 May 1995, in Saint-Andéol-le-Château, murder of the Bébien couple and two of their children.
Between 11 July 1995 and 17 October 1995, a series of attacks killed 8 people in Paris and Villeurbanne.
The perpetrator, Khaled Kelkal, was killed by law enforcement on 29 September 1995.
On 22 August 1995, Gilles Andruet, a 38-year-old chess champion was murdered in Saulx-les-Chartreux.
Eric Borel committed suicide on 24 September 1995.
From 27 January 1996 to 29 March 1996 in the Nord department, a series of robberies, three murders and an attempted attack.
The judicial aspect resulted in the conviction of Jean-Pierre Bourgeois and Annicka Brumark for pimping.
On 2 April 1996, Angela and Alain Hay were murdered by father and son Charles and Christophe Cretello in Rosenau.
Jean-Yves Morel was sentenced to life imprisonment in February 2000 by the Seine-Maritime Assize Court.
On 16 April 1996, 69-year-old Willy Pomonti was tortured and murdered at his home in La Celle-Saint-Cloud during a burglary.
From 23 April 1996 to 30 October 1996, Mamadou Traoré committed attacks on six women, two of whom were fatal, in Paris.
Mamadou Traoré was sentenced on 15 February 2000 to life imprisonment with a 22-year security period by the Paris Assize Court.
On 19 July 1996, 6-year-old Léo Balley disappeared in Taillefer. His body was never found.
Linked with the Disparus de l'Isère. Case unsolved as of 2025.
On 3 December 1996, in Paris, four people were killed and 91 others were injured in a terrorist attack on the Réseau Express Régional.
On 14 November 1996, Marion Wagon, a 10-year-old schoolgirl, disappeared a few hundred metres from her home in Agen.
On 27 December 1996, 20-year-old Christelle Blétry was found dead in Blanzy with 123 stab wounds by farm worker Pascal Jardin.
Pascal Jardin was sentenced on 2 February 2017 to life imprisonment with a 20-year security period by the Saône-et-Loire Assize Court.

116.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: On 27 February 2000, Suzanne Viguier disappeared in Toulouse. Her husband was convicted and later released and acquitted.
Jacques Plumain was sentenced on 12 April 2006 to life imprisonment with a 20-year security period by the Haut-Rhin Assize Court.
On 5 August 2000, Silja Trindler, a young Swiss tourist was murdered in Carcans. She was suffocated on the ground on a beach dune.
Between 2000 and 2007 in Valognes, Céline Lesage killed six newborns of whom she was the mother.
Céline Lesage was sentenced to 15 years of criminal imprisonment on 18 March 2010, by the Manche Assize Court. The consequences are unknown.
Fatima Idrahou, 23, was kidnapped and killed on 9 February 2001 by Marc Delpech, a bar owner in Perpignan.
Child sexual abuse. The case, which began in February 2001, will lead to the recognition of the innocence of the majority of the accused.
François Santoni, 41, politician, was assassinated with thirteen bullets on 17 August 2001 at a wedding in Monacia-d'Aullène.
On 2 November 2001, 40-year-old Éric Calers was shot dead in front of his home in Busnes.
A dismissal of the case was pronounced by the Pas-de-Calais Assize Court.
Rape, murder and incineration of Élodie Kulik on the night of 10–11 January 2002 in Tertry by several men.
On 7 October 2002, 41-year-old Sophie Berkmans, a rheumatologist, had her throat slit in her office in Valenciennes by Mohamed Medjahed.
On 7 February 2003, Monique Lejeune was murdered in Coulogne by Béatrice Matis, a former partner of her husband Claude.
Antoine Belmonte was killed on 22 February 2003 in Pantin in Seine-Saint-Denis with a gunshot through his door.
Poncé Gaudissard was sentenced on appeal on 19 March 2011 to life imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Var Assize Court.
On 11 April 2003, Xavier Flactif, his partner Graziella Ortolano and their three children were murdered by David Hotyat in Grand-Bornand.
David Hotyat was sentenced on 30 June 2006 to life imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Haute-Savoie Assize Court.
On 19 October 2004, 23-year-old Ghofrane Haddaoui, a French woman of Tunisian origin, was stoned to death in Marseille.
Commissioned assassination of hunter Marius Lac on 25 August 2004, following a case of animal poisoning.
Roland Bondonny committed suicide in prison after appealing his conviction.
The case is highly publicized, due to the celebrity of the father of one of the two victims and multiple twists and turns.
On 6 November 2004, Anthony Ashley-Cooper, 10th Earl of Shaftesbury was murdered in Cannes, by his brother-in-law Mohamed M'Barek.
Murder of a nursing assistant and a nurse on the night of 17–18 December 2004 at the Pau psychiatric hospital by Romain Dupuy.
Murder of Maryse Louvet in Mareuil-lès-Meaux on 15 January 2005, by his own daughter, Émilie, and her companion, Driss Sajdi.
Sajdi was previously sentenced to 20 years in prison for the murder of a young woman in 1991.
Murders of Christelle and Lucas Leroy [fr]
20 February 2005: Murder and dismemberment of Christelle Leroy, 26, and her son Lucas, 5, by his employer and lover Bérenger Brouns.
On 26 February 2005, Françoise Chabé was strangled at home in Humbercourt.
Ludovic, her husband, suspected of having killed her, is acquitted.
Murder of Nelly Cremel, 39 years old, in June 2005, near Reuil-en-Brie by Patrick Gateau and Serge Mathey.
Rape and murder of 24-year-old Audrey Jouannet on 13 September 2005, in Soisy-sur-Seine, by her caretaker Jean-Luc Cayez, a repeat rapist.
Robert Feliciaggi, 63, a Corsican politician, was shot dead in the parking lot of Ajaccio airport on 10 March 2006.
On 16 April 2006, 79-year-old Marcelle Bouvard was murdered in Ladoix-Serrigny by her great-nephew Geoffrey Perrin.
On 16 September 2009, Geoffrey Perrin was sentenced to 25 years in prison.
On 27 April 2007, 21-year-old Gaëlle Fosset, a student, was stabbed to death 66 times in her house in Saint-Germain-la-Campagne.
On 2 July 2007, Brahim Déby, son of Chadian President Idriss Déby was murdered in Courbevoie.
Abderrazzak Zibha was sentenced to 27 years in prison.
On 25 November 2007 in Creil, 23-year-old Anne-Lorraine Schmitt, was found dead in an RER D after being stabbed by Thierry Devé-Oglou.
Thierry Devé-Oglou was sentenced on 15 December 2010 to life imprisonment with a 22-year security period by the Val d'Oise Assize Court.
On 28 November 2007, 36-year-old Laurence Maille, was strangled by her companion John Szablewski in Farbus.
Facts revealed in March 2017 and May 2019, he claims his innocence despite the charges.
Hours after the abduction the body was found partly charred in the Chantilly forest.

117.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: Murder of 7-year-old Sophia Abid, in Brunstatt on 10 March 2003, asphyxiated by her mother Tania Parnisari.
Tania Parnisari was sentenced on 25 March 2008 to 18 years in prison at Strasbourg.
Kidnapping of 10-year-old Jonathan Coulom on 7 April 2004 in Saint-Brevin-les-Pins.
"Pierrot the Madman." First prisoner in France to be sentenced to life imprisonment.
Murder of Valentin Crémault, 11year-old, on the night of 28–29 July 2008, in Lagnieu, by Stéphane Moitoiret.
Infanticide of Marina Sabatier, 8 years old, in Écommoy on 6 August 2009 by his parents, Éric Sabatier and Virginie Darras.
Eric Sabatier died in prison four years after his trial.[246] The French government condemned the ECHR for failing to protect children.
In 2010, Pierre Nasica, 15, was stabbed to death in Belfort by his best friend, Yacine Sid.
Yacine Sid was sentenced to 20 years in prison because he confessed.

118.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: On 19 January 2011, 18-year-old Laetitia Perrais was murdered by Tony Meilhon in La Bernerie-en-Retz.
Tony Meilhon is sentenced on 5 June 2013, to life imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Loire-Atlantique Assize Court.
Dupont de Ligonnès murders and disappearance
On 6 April 2011, the quintuple murder of members of the Dupont de Ligonnès family at their home, in Nantes.
On 14 April 2011 murder of 50-year-old Colette Deromme, who was strangled by her ex-sister-in-law, Sylviane Fabre in Lorgues.
Sylviane Fabre was sentenced on 24 January 2014, to 30 years of criminal imprisonment by the Var Assize Court.
Yoni Palmier was sentenced on 16 April 2015 to life imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Essonne Assize Court.
Dominique Pelicot was sentenced to 20 years in prison.
Bettina Beau is sentenced on 23 May 2014 to 18 years of criminal imprisonment by the Loire Assizes.
Ludivine Chambet was sentenced on 23 May 2017 to 25 years of criminal imprisonment by the Savoie Assize Court.
Murders of Kévin Noubissi and Sofiane Tadbirt [fr]
On 28 September 2012 in Échirolles, murders of Kévin Noubissi, aged 21, and Sofiane Tadbirt, aged 22, in a park in Échirolles.
On 15 March 2013, the murder of Anne Barbot née Blin, by her husband Didier and his mistress Stéphanie Livet in Vritz.
Disappearance of Allison and Marie-José Benitez
On 14 July 2013 in Perpignan , mysterious disappearance of 19-year-old Allison Benitez and her 55-year-old mother Marie-José.
Francisco Benitez, the husband and father and prime suspect, committed suicide on 5 August 2013.
Édith Scaravetti was sentenced on 17 May 2019 to 10 years of criminal imprisonment by the Tarn-et-Garonne Assize Court.
Daniel Rudenko was sentenced on 24 June 2017 to 20 years of criminal imprisonment by the Vosges Assizes.
On 13 March 2016 in La Clayette, Valérie Bacot, a victim of domestic violence, shot her husband Daniel Polette in the back of the head.
Valérie Bacot was sentenced on 25 June 2021 to 4 years in prison, including 1 year in prison, by the Saône-et-Loire Assize Court.
On 7 August 2016 in Aubervilliers, 49-year-old Chinese fashion designer Chaolin Zhang died after being violently attacked by three youths.
On 4 December 2016 in Besançon, the disappearance and presumed murder of Narumi Kurosaki, a 21-year-old Japanese student.
Hubert Caouissin was sentenced on 7 July 2021 to 30 years of criminal imprisonment by the Loire-Atlantique Assize Court.
On 4 April 2017 in Paris, the anti-Semitic murder of Sarah Halimi who was stabbed in her home by Kobili Traoré and thrown from a balcony.
Kobili Traoré was declared criminally irresponsible by the Paris Assize Court on 19 December 2019.
On 28 October 2017 in Gray-la-Ville, murder of Alexia Daval by strangulation by her husband during an argument.
Jonathan Daval was sentenced on 21 November 2020 to 25 years of criminal imprisonment by the Haute-Saône Assize Court.
On 23 March 2018, in Paris, the anti Semitic murder of Mireille Knoll, who was stabbed in her home.
Yacine Mihoub was sentenced to life imprisonment with a 22-year security period by the Paris Assize Court.
On 29 July 2018 in Meylan, murder of Adrien Perez, killed with knives while he was helping a friend in the parking lot of a nightclub.
Jean-Marc Reiser was sentenced to life imprisonment with twenty-two years of security.
On 7 July 2019 in Mont-de-Marsan, Johanna Blanes, 24, a mother of a 19-month-old child, was found dead in the Laspécès tunnel.
Hussein Ahmed was sentenced on 10 June 2022 to 30 years of criminal imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Landes Assizes.
On 4 November 2019 in Agnetz, a priest, Roger Matassoli, was strangled and violently beaten by a young man whom he had sexually abused.
Alexandre V. was declared criminally irresponsible on 16 July 2021 by the Oise Assize Court.

119.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: On 4 June 2011 in Pau, murder of Alexandre Junca, a 13-year-old schoolboy by a stranger. His body dismembered by four accomplices.
Mickaël Baehrel is sentenced on 16 June 2016, to life imprisonment by the Pyrénées-Atlantiques Assize Court.
Le 6 novembre 2011 à Bellegarde, enlèvement, viol et meurtre d'Océane Luna, 8 ans, par Nicolas Blondiau.
Nicolas Blondiau est condamné le 17 février 2013, à la réclusion criminelle à perpétuité incompressible par les assises du Gard.
Le 16 novembre 2011 au Chambon-sur-Lignon, viol et meurtre d'Agnès Marin, 13 ans, par Mathieu Moulinas, 17 ans, récidiviste.
Mathieu Moulinas est condamné le 28 juin 2013, à la réclusion criminelle à perpétuité par les assises de Haute-Loire.
On 12 May 2013 in Clermont-Ferrand, 5-year-old Fiona Bourgeon, was murdered by her mother Cécile Bourgeon and her partner, Berkane Makhlouf.
On 15 April 2015 in Calais, 9-year-old Chloé Ansel was raped and murdered in a forest, by Zbigniew Huminski, a Polish worker.
Zbigniew Huminski, the perpetrator, committed suicide before his trial on 14 May 2017.
Nordahl Lelandais was sentenced to life imprisonment with a 22-year security term by the Isère Assize Court.
On 25 April 2018 in Wambrechies , kidnapping and sequestration, rape followed by murder of 13-year-old Angélique Six by David Ramault.
David Ramault was sentenced to life imprisonment with a 25-year security period by the Northern Assize Court.
X was sentenced to 18 years of criminal imprisonment by the Oise juvenile court.

120.title: list of criminal cases in France
table: From 1 to 12 March 2012 in Toulouse and Montauban, a series of firearm attacks left seven dead and six injured.
On 5 September 2012 in Chevaline , murder of three members of the same British family, a French cyclist is also shot dead.
Investigation ongoing. Case not solved as of 2025.
2013 triple murder of Kurdish activists in Paris
Omer Güney, the perpetrator, died in prison before his trial.
On 25 May 2013 in Nanterre, a knife attack against a French soldier, Cédric Cordier, by Alexandre Dhaussy.
Alexandre Dhaussy, the perpetrator of the acts, is declared criminally irresponsible.
From 15 to 18 November 2013, a gunman targeted a newspaper, a television station and a bank in Paris.
On 21 December 2014, in Dijon, a motorist deliberately drove his vehicle into the Christmas market, injuring thirteen people.
The perpetrator is declared not criminally responsible.
On 22 December 2014 in Nantes, Sébastien Sarron, 38, deliberately drove into the Christmas market and killed a 25-year-old man.
Sébastien Sarron, the perpetrator of the events, committed suicide on 13 April 2016 before his trial.
Chérif Kouachi, Saïd Kouachi, Amedy Coulibaly, the perpetrators of the acts, were killed on 9 January 2015 by the police.
Andreas Lubitz died in the plane crash on 24 March 2015.
Yassin Salhi, the perpetrator, committed suicide in prison before his trial on 22 December 2015.
On 21 August 2015 in Oignies, Ayoub El Khazzani attempted to carry out an attack on board a TGV train from Amsterdam to Paris.
Ayoub El Khazzani was sentenced on 17 December 2020 to life imprisonment with a security period of 22 years by the Paris Assize Court.
On 13 November 2015 in Paris, a series of terrorist attacks left 130 dead and 354 injured.
Larossi Abballa was killed by law enforcement on 14 June 2016.
On 26 July 2016, in Saint-Étienne-du-Rouvray, Father Jacques Hamel, 86, had his throat cut in his church. Another parishioner was injured.
Adel Kermiche and Abdel Malik Petitjean are shot dead by law enforcement.
Projet d'attentat de la cathédrale Notre-Dame de Paris
Attaque contre des militaires au Carrousel du Louvre
Le 3 février 2017 à Paris, attaque à la machette contre des militaires, l'un d'eux est blessé.
Colis piégé contre le FMI à Paris
Le 16 mars 2017 à Paris, un colis piégé explose au bâtiment du Fonds monétaire international, une personne est blessée.
Zyed Belgacem, auteur des faits est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Attentat sur l'avenue des Champs-Élysées du 20 avril 2017
Le 20 avril 2017 à Paris, un fonctionnaire de police est tué par balles sur l'avenue des Champs-Élysées.
Karim Cheurfi, auteur des faits est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Attaque contre des militaires à Levallois-Perret
Le 9 août 2017 à Levallois-Perret, cinq militaires sont blessés lors d'une attaque à la voiture bélier perpétré par Hamou Benlatrèche.
Attaque par arme blanche à la gare Saint-Charles de Marseille
Ahmed Hanachi est abattu par les forces de l'ordre.
Le 23 mars 2018 à Carcassonne et Trèbes une série d'attaques terroristes fait quatre morts et quinze blessés.
Radouane Lakdim est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Le 12 mai 2018 à Paris, Khamzat Azimov tue un passant de 29 ans, Ronan Gosnet, quatre autres sont blessés.
Khamzat Azimov est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Attentat du marché de Noël de Strasbourg
Le 11 décembre 2018 à Strasbourg, une attaque à l'arme à feux fait quatre morts et douze blessés sur le marché de Noël.
Chériff Chekatt, est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Le 4 février 2019 à Paris, un incendie déclenché criminellement fait dix morts et quatre-vingt-seize blessés.
Essia Boularès est condamnée le 23 février 2023 à 25 ans de réclusion criminelle.
Attentat de la prison de Condé-sur-Sarthe
Hanane Aboulhana est tuée par les forces de l'ordre.
Attentat de la rue Victor-Hugo de Lyon
Le 24 mai 2019 à Lyon, une attaque à la bombe fait 14 blessés dans une rue passante.
Attentat de la préfecture de police de Paris
Le 3 octobre 2019 à Paris, un agent de police radicalisé tue quatre de ses collègues à l'arme blanche avant d'être abattu.
Michael Harpon est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Attentat à la mosquée de Bayonne
Le 28 octobre 2019 à Bayonne, un retraité de 84 ans, tente de commettre un attentat à la bombe contre une mosquée.
Claude Sinké, auteur des faits meurt en prison avant son procès le 26 février 2020.
Le 3 janvier 2020 à Villejuif, un homme attaque au couteau des promeneurs dans un parc, faisant un mort et deux blessés.
Nathan Chiason est tué par les forces de l'ordre.
Le 4 avril 2020 à Romans-sur-Isère, un migrant soudanais attaque des passants dans la rue, il fait deux morts et cinq blessés.
Le 27 avril 2020 à Colombes, un homme radicalisé percute volontairement deux motards de la Police Nationale, les blessant grièvement.
Le 25 septembre 2020 à Paris, un migrant pakistanais tente de tuer au couteau deux journalistes devant les locaux de Charlie-Hebdo.
L'auteur des faits, Abdoullakh Anzorov, est aussitôt abattu par les forces de l'ordre.
Attentat de la basilique Notre-Dame de Nice
Le 29 octobre 2020 à Nice, un homme tue trois fidèles au couteau lors de l'attaque de la basilique.
